channel.title: Music now
channel.description:
Does anyone like the music now better than the rock n roll from the 70s and 80s?
I think I'm the only one left who likes all the old rock versus the new age of music. :rolleyes:
Anyways, anyone like any of these bands/musicians?
Bruce Spingsteen - Born to Run Lynrd Skynrd - Sweet Home Alabama Pink Floyd - "Money.. that's all I want" Steve Miller Band - The Joker Barry White - You're the first, my last, my everything lol Ohio Players, The - Fire Beatles, The - so many songs... Billy Joel - We didnt start the fire Guns N Roses - welcome to the jungle Hot Chocolate - You sexy thing Kiss - Rock N Roll all nite Led Zeppelin - Stairway to Heaven Ohio Express - Yummy yummy yummy Roy Orbinson - Pretty Woman Sex Pistols - Holidays in the sun Three Dog Night - One is the loneliest number Turtles, The - So happy together
Anyone know them? Most people will probably know 4 or 5 of those guys. :D
~Ron

cheesehunk your awesome. that is my kind of music right there. desperado by the eagles is one of my favs. i saw one error though. paradise city is not the name of the band thats the song lol. its paradise city by guns n roses

Oops. When I posted I accidently put a lot of the songs befoe the artists. I went back, and changed them, must have missed that one. Most of those bands I support them enough to actually buy a couple of there CD’s. I have the greatest hits of Guns N’ Roses, Queen, Aerosmith, Neil Young, Van Halen, Def Leppard, The Eagles, Led Zepplin, Pink Floyd, Rush, Supertramp, Nazareth, and some other ones. If I like there music a lot, I usually buy there CD’s.
